  "prompt": "Who were the leaders behind the Revolt of 1857?",
  "response": "The Revolt of 1857, also known as the Indian Mutiny, was a major uprising against the British East India Company's rule in India. Several leaders and prominent figures emerged during this uprising, representing various regions and communities. Some of the key leaders include:\n\n1. **Bahadur Shah II (Bahadur Shah Zafar):** The last Mughal emperor, who became a symbolic leader of the revolt in Delhi.\n2. **Rani Lakshmibai of Jhansi:** Known for her bravery and leadership, she played a crucial role in the rebellion in the Jhansi region.\n3. **Tantia Tope:** A close associate of Nana Sahib, Tantia Tope was a key military leader and strategist in the rebellion.\n4. **Nana Sahib:** He led the rebellion in Kanpur and was one of the prominent leaders opposing British rule.\n5. **Kunwar Singh:** A leader in Bihar, he was an elderly zamindar who actively participated in the revolt.\n6. **Begum Hazrat Mahal:** The queen of Awadh, she played a significant role in the revolt in the Lucknow region.\n7. **Bakht Khan:** A senior military commander who led the rebels in Delhi and was instrumental in the fight there.\n\nEach of these leaders contributed in different ways to the collective struggle against British colonial rule during the Revolt of 1857.",
